VL  - 4
IS  - 2
SP  - 307
EP  - 313
PY  - 1978
DA  - 1978/04/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(78)90008-9
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393278900089
AB  - This paper analyzes Cagan's model of hyperinflation under the assumption that the stochastic process generating the behavior of the money supply is such as to make adaptive expectations ‘rational,’ in the sense of Muth. The paper shows that when the coefficient of adjustment of expectations has the value implied by the assumption of adjustment of ‘rationality,’ the stability condition of Cagan's model is necessarily satisfied.
